subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Prostomium conical with transversal groove, without glandular ridges; three pairs of branchiae in two groups well separated from each other; paleae absent; buccal tentacles covered with ciliae, papillae absent; 
14
thoracic segments with notopodia; 
12
thoracic segments with neuropodia; 
14
abdominal segments with neuropodia, first two pairs of abdominal neuropodia of thoracic 
type
.
